  "prompt": "How do I get a bar graph on Excel to sort from highest to lowest?",
  "response": "To sort a bar graph from highest to lowest in Excel, follow these steps:\n\n1. Select your data range\n2. Click on the \"Insert\" tab\n3. Choose your bar graph type\n4. Click on the graph to select it\n5. Go to the \"Design\" tab under \"Chart Tools\"\n6. Click \"Select Data\"\n7. In the \"Select Data Source\" window, click \"Edit\"\n8. In the \"Edit Series\" window, click \"Switch Row/Column\" if needed\n9. Click \"OK\"\n10. Back in the \"Select Data Source\" window, click the \"Up\" or \"Down\" arrow to manually reorder\n11. Alternatively, click \"Sort\" and choose \"Largest to Smallest\"\n12. Click \"OK\"\n\nThe graph should now display bars sorted from highest to lowest.\n\nAnother quick method:\n1. Select your original data\n2. Go to \"Home\" tab\n3. Click \"Sort & Filter\"\n4. Choose \"Sort Largest to Smallest\"\n5. Recreate the graph with sorted data",
